### ============================================================
### MusicLab API Tests — AJT Semester Project
### Start backend first: .\start-supabase.ps1
### Install VS Code extension: "REST Client" by Huachao Mao
### ============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Unit 6/7 — REST API | Unit 4 — JPA
### GET all marketplace tracks from Supabase DB
### Expected: 200 OK, JSON array of track objects
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/market/tracks
Accept: application/json

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Unit 4 — ACID Transaction | Unit 8 — Strategy Pattern
### POST purchase track (Standard License — base price)
### Expected: 200 OK, transactionId in response
### Change trackId to match actual ID from GET /tracks response
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/market/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "buyerId": 1,
  "trackId": 1,
  "licenseType": "standard"
}

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Unit 4 — ACID Rollback Demo | Unit 8 — Strategy Pattern
### POST purchase track (Exclusive License — 10x price)
### Expected: 402 Payment Required (wallet has 5000, exclusive = 299.90)
### This proves @Transactional rollback works
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/market/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "buyerId": 1,
  "trackId": 1,
  "licenseType": "exclusive"
}

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Unit 2 — Java I/O (ObjectOutputStream serialization)
### Unit 4 — @Transactional persistence to PostgreSQL BYTEA
### POST save a music project (serialized to DB)
### Expected: 200 OK, projectId confirmed in response
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/studio/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "projectId": "demo-project-001",
  "userId": "1",
  "projectName": "AJT Demo Project",
  "bpm": 128,
  "tracks": [
    {
      "trackId": "track-001",
      "name": "Drum Loop",
      "volume": 0.8,
      "isMuted": false,
      "regions": [
        {
          "sampleId": "region-001",
          "startTime": 0.0,
          "duration": 4.0,
          "audioFileUrl": "http://localhost:8080/api/v1/audio/stream/sample.mp3"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Unit 2 — Java I/O (ObjectInputStream deserialization)
### GET load project back from DB (BYTEA → MusicProject)
### Expected: 200 OK, full project JSON reconstructed
### Use same projectId from the save request above
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/studio/load/demo-project-001
Accept: application/json

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Unit 2 — Java I/O Demo (serialize only, no DB)
### POST serialize a project to Base64 bytes
### Expected: 200 OK, serializedData (Base64 string) in response
### Copy the serializedData value for the deserialize test below
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/studio/serialize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "projectId": "serialize-test-001",
  "userId": "1",
  "projectName": "Serialization Test",
  "bpm": 120,
  "tracks": []
}

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Unit 2 — Java I/O Demo (deserialize Base64 back to object)
### POST deserialize — paste serializedData from above response
### Expected: 200 OK, project object reconstructed from bytes
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/studio/deserialize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serializedData": "PASTE_BASE64_FROM_SERIALIZE_RESPONSE_HERE"
}

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Unit 2 — Java NIO File I/O
### Unit 6/7 — REST multipart upload
### POST upload audio file
### NOTE: Cannot test in .http file — use the frontend UI instead
### Or use curl: curl -F "file=@yourfile.mp3" http://localhost:8080/api/v1/audio/upload
### Expected: 201 Created, storedFilename + streamUrl in response
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Unit 2 — Java NIO streaming
### GET stream audio file (after upload)
### Replace {filename} with storedFilename from upload response
### Expected: 200 OK, audio/mpeg or audio/wav Content-Type
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/audio/stream/sample.mp3
Accept: audio/mpeg

###
